erties-in-cpp-cli.md) can only be declared within a managed or Windows Runtime type. Native types do not support the `property` keyword.  \n  \n## Example  \nThe following sample generates C3813 and shows how to fix it:  \n  \n```cpp  \n// C3813.cpp  \n// compile by using: cl /c /clr C3813.cpp  \nclass A  \n{  \n   property int Int; // C3813  \n};  \n  \nref class B  \n{  \n   property int Int; // OK - declared within managed type  \n};  \n```"}